original: Jansson, Gustaf Emanuel, läroverksadjunkt, Halmstad, f. 14/5/85 i Halmstad. — Stud:ex. i Halimistad 04, fil. kand. i Lund 06. Vik. 1’eiktior i Halmstad 06 o. 07, e. lär. i Falun 09-10, i Halmstad 10-11, vik. adj. där part. 12, e. o. lektor i Eskilstuna 12-14, adj. i fysik o. miatem^. v. Halmsitadis h. a. 1. ■sed. 13.
translated: Jansson, Gustaf Emanuel, high school teacher, Halmstad, born on May 14th, 1885 in Halmstad. He completed his high school studies in Halmstad in 1904 and obtained a bachelor's degree in Lund in 1906. He worked as a substitute teacher in Halmstad in 1906 and 1907, and as a regular teacher in Falun from 1909 to 1910, in Halmstad from 1910 to 1911, and as a substitute teacher there in 1912 before becoming a permanent lecturer in Eskilstuna from 1912 to 1914. He taught physics and mathematics at the Halmstad high school from 1913. He got married in 1913.
